commentPostTextItems.html: Dhaniram, who retired hurt, doesn't bother to come back out to bat and that completes proceedings at St Lucia, with a comprehensive victory for New Zealand. They are certainly looking like strong contenders at this early stage of the competition. Canada's performances in the group just got better, however, and they did very well today, giving the Kiwis some decent practice. Davison was at his brilliant best, too, with some entertainment early on.

Thanks ever so much for joining us today, hope you've enjoyed it as much as we have. Do come back tomorrow when India take on Sri Lanka in a must-win game for them, while West Indies play Ireland in what promises to be another interesting match.
